M|Veri|Befo|
M|Veri|it|[ ] Every new fn/method has a tst
M|Veri|it|[ ] Watched each tst fail before implementing
M|Veri|it|[ ] Each tst failed for expected reason (feature missing, not typo)
M|Veri|it|[ ] Wrote minimal code to pass each tst
M|Veri|it|[ ] All tests pass
M|Veri|it|[ ] Output pristine (no er, warnings)
M|Veri|it|[ ] Tests use real code (mocks only if unavoidable)
M|Veri|it|[ ] Edge cases and er covered
M|Veri|tx|Can't check all boxes? You skipped TDD. Start over.
M|When|tx|\| Problem \| Solution \|
M|When|tx|\|---------\|----------\|
M|When|tx|\| Don't know how to tst \| Write wished-for ap. Write assertion first. Ask your human partner. \|
M|When|tx|\| tst too complicated \| ds too complicated. Simplify if. \|
M|When|tx|\| Must mock everything \| Code too coupled. Use dependency injection. \|
M|When|tx|\| tst setup huge \| Extract helpers. Still complex? Simplify ds. \|
M|Debu|tx|Bug found? Write failing tst reproducing it. Follow TDD cycle. tst proves fix and prevents regression.
M|Debu|tx|Never fix bugs w/o a tst.
M|Test|When|
M|Test|it|Testing mock behavior instead of real behavior
M|Test|it|Adding tst-only methods to production classes
M|Test|it|Mocking w/o understanding dependencies
M|Fina|tx|```
M|Fina|tx|Production code → tst exists and failed first
M|Fina|tx|Otherwise → not TDD
M|Fina|tx|```
M|Fina|tx|No exceptions w/o your human partner's permission.